title: Counter-Strike 2 - Official Launch Trailer
description:
Counter-Strike 2 is here!

A free upgrade to CS:GO, Counter-Strike 2 marks the beginning of an exciting new chapter and the largest technical leap in Counter-Strike's history. Built on the Source 2 engine, Counter-Strike 2 is modernized with realistic physically-based rendering, state of the art networking, upgraded Community Workshop tools, and more.

Download and play today!

Tournament footage used with permission of ESL and BLAST.

title: Assassin's Creed Mirage: Official Cinematic Launch Trailer
description:
Become the Master Assassin.
Assassin's Creed Mirage, available on October 5, 2023.

In Assassin’s Creed Mirage, you are Basim, a cunning street thief with nightmarish visions, seeking answers and justice. After an act of deadly retribution, Basim flees Baghdad and joins an ancient organization – The Hidden Ones. As he learns their mysterious rituals and powerful tenets, he will hone his unique abilities, discover his true nature, and come to understand a new Creed – one that will change his fate in ways he never could have imagined.

title: Alan Wake 2 Hands-On Preview (New Gameplay)
description:
Tam and Lucy recently played a few hours of Remedy’s upcoming psychological horror, Alan Wake 2. They played as both FBI Agent Saga Anderson in the quaint town of Watery, and as Alan, trapped in the Dark Place.

It's been 13 long years since the original Alan Wake, and the sequel to the cult classic has taken our favorite beleaguered writer, and dropped him right into the middle of a psychological horror that he needs to write his way out of. Meanwhile, FBI Agent Saga Anderson makes for Bright Falls to investigate the mystery of a series of ritualistic murders, and unwittingly gets embroiled in the supernatural horror that Alan is at the centre of.

At a recent preview event, Tamoor and Lucy played 3 hours of Alan Wake II, playing as both Saga and Alan. In Saga's mission, Local Girl, they got to grips with the Case Board and Profiling mechanics in the Mind Place. Alan's mission, Room 665 took them to the Oceanview Hotel, where they got to try out using the Angel Lamp to Light Shift,
